msg: Checkpoint some work regarding specialized sorting of paths for the
Ev1 drive within the shims. This revision sets up the mechanics for
sorting the changes and passing them into the path_driver.
However: 27 tests failed with the new sorting. Falling back to the
normal sort mechanic returns to the single merge 105 failure.
(sort_deletes_first): new function to sort paths where the deletes
are delivered before any further adds, in order to account for
(get_sorted_paths): helper function to extract a proper sort-order
(drive_changes): use the new get_sorted_paths() helper. because it
doesn't quite work, resort the paths. use the new path_driver
